    "description": "Dedicated Freight Corridor invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Distribution Manager at our Mysuru location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Dedicated Freight Corridor:\nDedicated Freight Corridor is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Oversee end-to-end logistics operations for timely delivery\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n• Implement warehouse management systems (WMS) and track KPIs\n• Handle customs clearance for import and export shipments\n• Track shipments in real-time and resolve delivery exceptions\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Arch / M.Arch from recognized institution\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in TMS\n• Proficiency in Last Mile Delivery\n• Proficiency in GPS Tracking Systems\n• Proficiency in Data Analytics\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in WMS\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Learning & development budget\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Dedicated Freight Corridor!",
